roemetz.gui

Class RMGUInterface

  • java.lang.Object
    • roemetz.gui.RMGUInterface

  • public class RMGUInterface
extends java.lang.Object
    This class describes the interface for iRoeMetz application. It contains a panel for inputting means, components of variance, and experiment size. The next panel performs multiple simulation experiments based on the input. The last panel estimates the components of variance for the given input.
    Author:
    Rohan Pathare

                 double[][] t01,
                 double[][] t10,
                 double[][] t11,
                 double[] auc,
                 java.lang.String filename,
                 long l)
        Writes the results of a simulation experiment as ROC scores to a text file, formatted to be read by iMRMC or equivalent software
        Parameters:
        t00 - Matrix for normal cases, modality 0
        t01 - Matrix for normal cases, modality 1
        t10 - Matrix for disease cases, modality 0
        t11 - Matrix for disease cases, modality 1
        auc - AUCs of experiment1
        filename - Filename prefix (is a timestamp) for a particular batch of output files
        l - The number of this particular experiment in the batch
